# ============================================================================
# Local-only overlays — never committed to the Asura repo.
#
# Two things install themselves into this working tree but must never
# leak into a push:
#
# 1. Obsidian-mind vault — personal note-taking layer (brain/, work/,
#    org/, perf/, reference/, thinking/, bases/) plus its config files
#    (Home.md, AGENTS.md, GEMINI.md, CLAUDE.md, vault-manifest.json,
#    .obsidian/, .shardmind/, etc.) and the cross-tool agent dirs
#    (.codex/, .gemini/). Installed by the obsidian-mind v6.1 template.
#
# 2. Claude Code skill plugins — anything dropped under .claude/ or
#    .claude-plugin/ (ui-ux-pro-max-skill, agents, commands, sub-skills,
#    settings) is local tooling, not project source.
#
# To commit a *new* Claude Code skill or vault note back into Asura,
# override the rule for that specific file with an inverse pattern (`!`).
# ============================================================================

# Obsidian-mind vault: top-level dirs
/bases/
/brain/
/org/
/perf/
/reference/
/thinking/
/work/

# Obsidian-mind vault: top-level config / overlay files
/Home.md
/AGENTS.md
/GEMINI.md
/CLAUDE.md
/vault-manifest.json
/.gitignore.asura.bak
/.mcp.json
/.shardmindignore

# Obsidian-mind vault: hidden config dirs
/.codex/
/.gemini/
/.obsidian/
/.shardmind/
/.Trash/
/.qmd/

# Obsidian-mind vault: helper scripts dir (Asura's repo doesn't ship one)
/scripts/

# Claude Code project-local skills / agents / commands / plugin metadata
/.claude/
/.claude-plugin/
